<item>
            <title>[WICKET-3611] Redirect to Buffer makes one redirect too much</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3611</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems the default redirect strategy makes one redirect more than needed.&lt;br/&gt;
Here is the scenario: there is a page A with a (non-ajax) link that sets page B as response page (setResponsePage(B.class).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 1.4 this leads to two http requests: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;one to the A&apos;s link listener&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;and another redirecting to page B&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In 1.5 there are three:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;one to the A&apos;s link listener&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;another redirecting to page B&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;and yet another one again redirecting to B&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;With &quot;redirect to render&quot; strategy in both versions just two requests are issued.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
